BFN 

  [Excerpts] Belgrade, 10 Apr (TANJUG) -- Vitaliy Churkin, 
Russian President Yeltsin's special envoy for Yugoslavia and 
Russian deputy foreign minister, arrived in Belgrade this 
evening. 
  Upon his arrival, Churkin said that a new situation has been 
created after the attack launched by NATO planes on Serb 
positions near Gorazde. 
  The Russian president's special envoy stressed that he would 
be in contact with Moscow during the night. Churkin is expected 
to meet Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic tomorrow. [passage 
omitted] 
  It has been learned that Churkin is planning to visit Zagreb 
and Sarajevo where he is expected to meet Croatian and Muslim 
officials. 

